column1: OSF | Wave 9.1.1 | ACC1 | ACC2| UM | Orders are not getting processed E2E from ACC1 and status updated in IAV as  Verzögert
column41:
Placing orders from Retail/Telesales channel in ACC1/test1B/UAT01 , ACC2/Test2B OSF frontend we can able to submit the order with OSF ID creation. But IAV order status updated as *Verzögert and* below error updated  *Test orders :* ACC1/test1b: Retail New: 932407/8504698,  932375/8504690 , Telesales New: 932255 /8504688 ACC2/test2b: Telesales : OSF ID: 1154111/6200364 *Automatische Verarbeitung verschoben: Service Minerva temporär nicht verfügbar (Unexpected response: Weblogic Bridge Message

Failure of Web Server bridge:

No backend server available for connection: timed out after 10 seconds or idempotent set to OFF or method not idempotent.
).* *Steps to Re-Produce:* 1) Login to OSF Frontend application Retail/Telesales 2) Search with UM address and check severability working 3) Select the any of the UM Cable Broadband product and do checkout. 4) Enter all the customer information(name, DOB, email, Telephone, etc) and proceed 5) Proceed the order till OSF ID creation. 6) once OSF ID creation done check the the web order in to IAV portal test1b. 7) Check order status is updated as complete and sent to UM Backend or not. {*}Actual Results{*}:  Test1b-IAV portal Order status updated as *Verzögert* and order not reached to UM BE *Expected Results:* test1b - IAV status should be completed and UME customer number details should be updated , than order  should be processed E2E in UM backend successfully
column229: E2E UM order not able to processed
column474: the root cause was a missing dependency update propagation. DomainTypeDefinitions library was updated with new portal names like PARTNERPUB. This new version was updated in aletheia. It was not updated in MinervaAdapter. MinervaAdapter calls aletheia to get the product setup. It now got the portal PARTNERPUB from aletheia, which was unkown to Minerva and failed. We updated the DomainTypeDefinitions library in MinervaAdapter to fix it.

column1: OSF | Wave 9.1.1 | ACC1/2/3 | FN GetProductAvailability failing with VFP-00005 error for 'ONKZ_QUERY' parameter
column41:
*Issue description:*

getting below error while doing customer search

*Error in VFP response:* Pflichtparameter (abhängig): Wenn der Parameter 'PHONE_NUMBER_EXISTING_CUSTOMER' angegeben ist, muss der Parameter 'ONKZ_QUERY' ebenfalls angeben werden.

 

Use case: Existing customer Fixnet shows availability GLAS/DSL/LTE as grey although the address itself is having the availability

*Test Data:* customer no. 1926427263

*Steps to reproduce:*

1.Login to Retail/Telesales channel

2. Do legacy customer using customer no.

3. check  getresponse in logs

Problem – Error Code

Output for FN GetProductAvailability : <xml-fragment>
<ResultCode>VFP-00005</ResultCode>
*<ResultText>Pflichtparameter (abhängig): Wenn der Parameter 'PHONE_NUMBER_EXISTING_CUSTOMER' angegeben ist, muss der Parameter 'ONKZ_QUERY' ebenfalls angeben werden.</ResultText>*
<NumberHits>0</NumberHits>
</xml-fragment>

It seems OGW is missing to send areaCode to Backend and therefore we are getting this error.

Specification (very old)
|ONKZ_QUERY|Conditionally|0[1-9][0-9]+|Area code for the ASB-Suche with leading '0' (e.g. '069').
Mandatory, when one of the parameter CITY and PLZ in the object VFP_ADDRESS_QUERY is empty.
Mandatory, if the parameter PHONE_NUMBER_EXISTING_CUSTOMER in the object O_VFP_EXISTING_CUSTOMER_QUERY is passed.|

 

There have been ACC/ SIT tickets in 2018 for the same and it got fixed by OGW but the tickets are too old to find (Z_PRT00089777A/ PRT00088105A)

 

 

Its already present in production seems like last week, but I did not find an amdocs fix which went live on 11{^}th{^} of November, which could have caused it.

column787:
07/Jan/25 7:02 PM;alka.kshirsagar2@vodafone.com;Mail from Maro:

 

Hi all,

 

concerning the logic of providing the parameter in the service availability call for existing customers:
 # If a TASI exist for the customer this one has to be provided (which works currently)
 # If no TASI is found (which is the case for all LTE customers) the existing phone number has to be send -> to be provided as phonenumber

           2.1 And in addition the ONKZ value -> to be provided as areaCode

 

The part 2.1 seems to be missing

 

During the first waves we had the discussion how the parameters should be filled

 

Please check if the parameter is already missing in Omnius or only on OGW side.

 

Regards,

Marco

4) Submit order

column781:
17/Dec/24 7:14 PM;nina.pickl@vodafone.com;Hi [~anton.ustimenko@vodafone.com],

display in IAV is not part of the cable *backend* processing.

Once on OSF Order recieves CAB backen, the order ID is shown in IAV.

But afterwards the cable *logistic* backend processing of the order should be stared with the OSFAnyDelivery Tool from Jens(letter generation, device provisioning, workorder closing...).

This toll does not work atm because weborder db changes were done on test1b and these changes are not yet included into OsfAnyDelivery tool. E-mail is already sent to Jens. This Bug is only for tracking proposal. ;;;

Issue has been discussed with bas and we come to solution, which is as below.

During the populate_additionalDb step we are thinking to update the catalog_tables.xml file as like we do during the resetModule upgrade process.

This should make the update similar and should solve our problem currently we are facing.

 

This change or fix cannot be fixed immediately as it needs quite development and more testing effort after the fix, as we don't have such env setup like ACC where we have separate Web & Script servers maintained. 29/Jan/25 12:03 PM;vikash.saurav@vodafone.com;SunilkumarCM added a comment
 
 
Hi All

I discussed this issue further with Waseem and discussed few possible solution.

Solution: we need to keep the *catalog_tables.xml* file on some central place and create symlink of it on all servers like Web servers, Script Servers, API servers, to avoid file differences between Web & Script servers, etc

Ideally it should be treated/managed to create symlink similar to the Cable artifact file we currently do after pcat import.

*Steps to follow to create symlink.*
 # Ideally we need to perform this Symlink create after the completion of PCAT import on Sandbox environment.

 # Then copy the file from Sandbox environment from the path \{{DOCROOT}}/app/etc/catalog_tables.xml and keep it on some central place

*Note: This copy file and create symlink should happen before we start the Publish activity.(Ideally after completion of PCAT import and before Publish start)*
 # Then start the publish process.

We need to discuss  so that this can be done on ACC and verified. KIndly schedule call for the same;;;

column803:
03/Feb/25 6:53 PM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;The issue is caused by the new Package type TV for Fusion C - as we have the parser and the new Fusion C catalogue on both ACC1, ACC2 and in production, the issue happened on all 3 ENV already.

TechM is working on a solution from code and infra side, but its not mandatory for production Go Live Wave 9.2 as issue is already present in production and temporarily solved. Unless no new package type will come up, it should not fail anymore.

Issue is caused by the solution for faster PCAT Publish (reduction of the publish downtime). Within this solution there is a design gap

reset modules are running on the application but its getting updated on Webservers only -> files on the script servers are not updated. There is a configuration in backend to connect to Webserver or Scriptserver and for security reasons we need to get the files from Scriptservers and cannot take it from Webservers

-> Solution will be prepared by TechM, once its ready we align on a testing slot as we should not disturb release test activities in remaining last 2 weeks;;;

12/May/25 7:10 PM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;Latest feedback from TechM:

*Issue:*

This issue occurred due to mismatch in table on Sandbox and script server. The mismatch happened because “catalog_tables.xml” update on sandboxes is not reflected on other server.

 

{*}Solution{*}:

As part of this solution  we create a Symlink of  “catalog_tables.xml” and put in a central location so that  central location has always have updated   file of  “catalog_tables.xml”, whenever deployment will happen on other server it will pick this file “catalog_tables.xml”  from  central location  and not from pkg itself  so that other server will have  Web, Script & API etc will have updated file as well  so that when plm run from script server it will not  have mismatch of table issue  due to updated file there.

 

{*}Impact{*}: it will not have any impact since tested in ST but ACC we can see once deployment will be done.;;;

column842:
13/Jun/25 12:16 PM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;Latest feedback from Waseem:

Based on the latest call below is the solution:

OSE deployment on Sandbox:
 # Check if catalog_tables.xml is present under the shared location (for example in ACC1: /opt/SP/websync/PRD_DATA/omnius/ACC1/catalogue/)
 # IF file is present, then create a symlink for the file in app/etc/catalog_tables.xml towards sharedpath/catalog_tables.xml for example in ACC1: /opt/SP/WEB_DATA/ACC1/omnius/osf-dintib-acc1/app/etc/catalog_tables.xml is symlinked to /opt/SP/websync/PRD_DATA/omnius/ACC1/catalogue/catalog_tables.xml file.
 # IF file is not present then COPY the catalog_tables.xml file from the tar package to the shared location (for example in ACC1 on the location /opt/SP/websync/PRD_DATA/omnius/ACC1/catalogue/catalog_tables.xml) and then create a symlink same as step 2.
 # *Either step 2 is taken or step 3, app/etc/catalog_tables.xml file should always be a symlink to the sharedlocation/catalog_tables.xml file at the end of SANDBOX deployment.*

OSE deployment on webser, api server, script server or any deployment other than SANDBOX deployment.
 # Create a symlink for the file app/etc/catalog_tables.xml to the file present in the sharedlocation/catalog_tables.xml. For example on ACC1 the file /opt/SP/WEB_DATA/ACC1/omnius/osf-telesales-int-acc1/app/etc/catalog_tables.xml is symlinked to /opt/SP/websync/PRD_DATA/omnius/ACC1/catalogue/catalog_tables.xml file

This will ensure that the changes done to catalog_tables.xml during PLM is also available in the webserver or script or api as the change is done to the file on the sharedlocation.


-> permanent solution Kevin is working on;;;

04/Dec/24 3:41 PM;anton.ustimenko@vodafone.com;Last comment from Frederick in PSTBUG:

When investigating this bug it only occured on the ACC1 and not the ACC2.
The cable posting rules are out of the question, as they are not even executed when clicking the gigakombi button.

We also checked the relevant input files on cable and mobile pcat side (Bundles.xml).
Diffing the involved cable products easily showed no significant changes.
The relevant bundle rule in this case is GK1a gigakombi bundle rule that has not changed in a very long time.
In particular I specifically checked exactly the imported version of the Bundles.xml.
This is why I wrote that this is an OSF issue.

Diving into OSFs backend shows that the problem is indeed not the input, but rather how it was processed and came out on the other side.

but occured on ACC1

column1: OSF | Wave 9.1 and Wave 9.1.1 | ACC1 and ACC3 | PR | DSL orders are stuck at XDSL SO Mgmt 3 process in OPM
column41:
While performing Today's sanity in ACC1 and ACC3 environment, we have observed that DSL orders are stuck at XDSL SO Mgmt 3 process in OPM

Error description
 
FATAL 2012: database execute function failed in RQ=223440212 StoredProcedure=VFP_IF.check_ags_n Errortext=VFP aufrufen und die Daten speichern  ORA-12514: TNS:listener does not currently know of service requested in connect descriptor stack:ORA-06512: at "OPM.VFP_IF", line 1608
ORA-06512: at "OPM.VFP_IF", line 2257
 
Steps to reproduce:
1. Login to Telesales/retail channel
2. Select DSL tariff
3. Proceed to checkout
4. Add customer details
5. Submit the order
6. Perform OPM
7. Verify order's status at XDSL SO Mgmt 3
 
Expected Result:
Order should move ahead to next state from XDSL SO Mgmt 3
 
Actual result:
Orders are getting stuck at XDSL SO Mgmt 3 state in OPM



Test data 

Telesales – 912249 / VDE5601924396

Retail- 912251 / VDE7601924397

column41:

3. Proceed to checkout
4. Add customer details
5. Submit the order
6. Perform OPM
7. Verify order's status at CLR-TAL-Auftr-bearb state
 
Expected Result:
Order should move ahead to next state from CLR-TAL-Auftr-bearb state
 
Actual result:
Orders are getting stuck at CLR-TAL-Auftr-bearb state in OPM with 'TAL-12514' error code

column1: OSF | WAVE 9.1.1 | ACC3 | Invalid Error Banner for Expired MTAN & Exceeded Attempts for MTAN Authentication
column41:
We observed that we are getting Invalid Error Banner for Expired MTAN & Exceeded Attempts for MTAN Authentication 

 

*Steps to Reproduce:*
 # Login to ACC3-Telesales with a user who has a role where the permission "MTAN+20FX" is assigned
 # Search for Mobile customer
 # Agent proceeds to authenticate customer on search result page.
 # MTAN authentication widow will appear
 # Agent enter the MTAN code after expiration.

 

*Expected Result:*

410
EN: MTAN code has expired
DE: MTAN ist abgelaufen

*Actual Result:* 

EN: mTAN Authentication is not possible for the customer at the moment.
Next authentication method being offer here
DE: mTAN-Authentifizierung ist für den Kunden derzeit nicht möglich.
Nächste Authentifizierungsmethode wird hier angeboten.

 

!image-2024-10-28-16-30-31-375.png|width=522,height=262!

*Test Data:*  KS_118013774
column229: Incorrect error messages for Authentication failure will create confusion & misleading Agent.
column474: No change required, Works as Designed
column779:
29/Oct/24 2:22 PM;vikash.saurav@vodafone.com;Charul Gupta added a comment -
 
[~krishnkumar.satpute@vodafone.com] 
 
The above mentioned behaviour is implemented according to the US [!https://bmcomviva.atlassian.net/images/icons/issuetypes/story.svg!VFDED1FTS-6025: Part -3 : OMNIUS, CUST : As an Agent, i wanted to authenticate via mTAN in harmonized way, so that if mTAN fails system offer next possible authentication method in harmonized manner.Done|https://bmcomviva.atlassian.net/browse/VFDED1FTS-6025] 
https://jira.sp.vodafone.com/browse/OAF-806



_*Technical skip: other then 200/201 Red banner with generic message*_
 # If next auth method
EN: mTAN Authentication is not possible for the customer at the moment.
Next authentication method being offer here
*DE: mTAN-Authentifizierung ist für den Kunden derzeit nicht möglich.*
*Nächste Authentifizierungsmethode wird hier angeboten.*

Which further mean if we have error code 410 and 429 also then error message
*DE: mTAN-Authentifizierung ist für den Kunden derzeit nicht möglich.Nächste Authentifizierungsmethode wird hier angeboten.* will come along with next available authentication method. 

Hence this bug is not valid.;;;

hence, considering work as design we are closing this defect.

column1: On-Hold | OSF | Wave 9.1 | Regression | A Sky ticket is created at a DSL tariff change with SecureNet in the inventory
column41:
Test data:
Environment: ACC1 

Channel: Telesales + Retail

DSL PCAT: OSF-20241027_Version_391_FN_2024_10_10

Test data: 001956928712

 

*Please note:* this bug is already in Production

 

{+}Actual result{+}: A Sky ticket is created at a DSL tariff change with SecureNet in the inventory – > Missing *refComponentId in Component for SecureNet*

 

+Expected result:+ No Sky ticket should be created at a DSL tariff change with SecureNet in the inventory

 

+Steps to reproduce:+
 * search for a DSL customer with SecureNet in the inventory on ACC1, e.g.: 001956928712
 * click on "Meine Produkte >> DSL package >> Paket ändern"
 * select a new DSL tariff, e. g.: "[R708.2000000020-24] GigaZuhause 250 DSL"
 * click on the button "Weiter"

– > "[I1414ISN01] Secure Net+" and "[GS_SN_3x3_99[br]] 3 Monate Rabatt auf Secure Net+" stay in the inventory – > *OK*

!image-2024-10-15-10-42-19-205.png!
 * create the order

OSF Order ID: 889055

– > Sky Ticket is created

*Service Name*
FNSubmitOrder
 
*Error Code*
SIDCOM-ERROR
 
*Error Description*
An error was encountered while invoking FN-CreateFNPOrder WS. Details [Error_Code: SIDCOM-ERROR, Error_Message: ERROR COM0000: Sorted SOM is INVALID! nullcvc-complex-type.4: Attribute 'ID' must appear on element 'secureNet'., Error_Type: , Error_Sevirity: , Error_Information: ]

 

[~marco.abraham01@vodafone.com] has already analyzed the bug:

 
 * at ILS no information about SecureNet is provided to the Backend (Also at a cancellation of SecureNet nothing os provided to the Backend)

 * missing refComponentId in Component for SecureNet in RetrieveCustomerInfo - Mode2 logs

For *other components* there is a refComponentId, e. g.:  

!image-2024-10-15-11-00-06-711.png!

For the SecureNet component there is no refComponentId. There should be a refComponentId *10* for SecureNet, like:

!image-2024-10-15-11-01-38-816.png!

column1: ON-HOLD | OSF | Wave9.0 | ACC2 | GeteSIMInformation service is not triggering for S2S multi order line update
column41:
While performing New activation of Esim compatible with as shipping order deliver to your own shop flow , We have observed,  GeteSIMInformation request is not triggering for E-SIM with Ship2Store order in case of multiple order line ids.

*Steps to Reproduce:*
 # Login to Omnius as Retail channel.
 # Add more than one E-SIM compatible Package and Proceed to checkout.
 # Select E-SIM in New connection section.
 # Select Shipping order - Delivery to your own shop
 # Submit order and send for VORAS processing
 # Observe OrderLineID is missing in setorder status after BE processing

 

 

*Actual Result:*  GeteSIMInformation request is not triggering for E-SIM

*Expected Result:* GeteSIMInformation request should trigger

 

(Raised the ticket for tracking purpose)
column229: Customer ESIM Information will be missing from KIAS for order with multiple orderline ID.

column1: OSF | Wave 9.0 | ACC2 | 5930 email is getting generated for prolongation mobile with esim having both blocking permission.
column41:
We have observed that 5930 email is getting generated for prolongation mobile with esim having both blocking permission in retail channel.

{color:#ffab00}*Both blocking permission: "ENABLE_ESIMSERIALNUMBER" & "DISABLE_ESIMPUSH".*{color}

Normally 5930 email should not be generated with above scenario.

 

*Steps to reproduce:*
 # Login to Retail channel
 # perform mobile prolongation with esim customer
 # select esim hardware
 # In new connection section, select New sim and enter sim number.
 # submit the order
 # Observe the issue.

 

*Expected result:* 5930 email should not be generated for this scenario.

*Actual result:* 5930 email is getting generated for this scenario.

24/Dec/24 3:22 PM;robert.goebbels@vodafone.com;Hi,

 

we have discussed this defect together with Gaurab from Amdocs in one of the sessions, last week, in which we analysed E2E the expected behaviour and discussed some defects.

Also Waldemar and Michael Heller were involved.

 

1. What I miss in this error description is the EXACT activities, that the agent/tester has done.

my assumption is:  the agent has selected the unsharp sim swap (which is a possibility in Retail, that will disappear with the esim Push Epic, but is still available if the permission for insert sim_serial_number is set (I think)

so..  question:  did indeed the tester select the UNSHARP SIMSWAP?

 

Because:

IF Agent selects UNSHARP SIMSWAP, 

THEN SubmitOrder.SIMCARD = E (as it always was)

and... OGW is triggered to send the emails when SIMCARD =E

(so.. this is not correct)

 

AS AGREED WITH GAURAB :

Amdocs will change/improve the software:

OGW will not only check for SIMCARD = E,  but will also check whether the NEW_SIM_SERIAL_NUMBER is not populated.

only then the emails will be sent;;;
column803:
30/Dec/24 5:25 PM;ajay.yashwantbhavar@vodafone.com;-> did indeed the tester select the UNSHARP SIMSWAP?

Hello [~robert.goebbels@vodafone.com] In both cases, Email is getting triggered, As the parameter SIMSWAP reason is always handed over to OGW with the value VR (Unsharp) even if the agent has selected Sharp (VS) in front end.

Please find below screenshot from submit order request.

!image-2024-12-30-17-19-16-405.png|width=485,height=600!;;;
column804: 30/Dec/24 9:12 PM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;[~robert.goebbels@vodafone.com]  please check the comment from Ajay and let us know if anything still unclear ;;;
column805: 08/Jan/25 12:04 PM;gaurav.lanjewar1@vodafone.com;Hi [~robert.goebbels@vodafone.com]  could you please check & share your observations.;;;
column806:
13/Jan/25 8:46 PM;robert.goebbels@vodafone.com;So final outcome  (my understanding)

Summary: 
 * works as (wrongly) designed
 * Amdocs will fix this without the need of a Change Request
 ** OGW will not only check:  is SIMTYPE E, in order to trigger the emails, BUT also check if the SIMNumber is empty

 

Details:

RETAIL channel; blocking permissions set:
 * agent must therefore insert SIM number (instead of SIMTYPE) AND
 * agent has possiblity to select Sharp vs unsharp simswap 

Omnius sends in submit Order
 * SIMYPE E, because agent has selected unsharp SIMSWAP (not clear to me, but it looks like Omnius also sends SIMTYPE E, if the agent selected sharp SIMSWAP, if I understand the comments right). 
 * SIMSERIAL number (because Agent has inserted a (physical) SIMnumber 

OGW triggers 5910 and/or 5930 email although the agent has inserted a (physical)  sim number

 

Solution: Even if Omnius sends SIMTYPE E,  OGW must also check, if a SIMNumber is provided  in submitOrder.  if the simnumber is empty, only then trigger the emails 

-->  as aligned with Gaurab some weeks ago

 

 ;;;

column1: OSF| Wave 9.0.2| ACC3 | NEW CR required_ SPIN_CAB data is not displayed in DWH Extract Customer_Auth.CSV file
column41:
We are performing DWH Scenario for MTAN CR 760 Part 1. We have observed the below issues
 
Cable customer authenticated using SPIN_CAB is not coming in the CSV file.

     
*Steps to Reproduce:*
 # Login to {*}Server{*}: ssh [dynalacc@deosabivr|mailto:dynalacc@deosabivr].dc-ratingen.de
 # Go to the path /opt/SP/WEB_DATA/ACC3/omnius/osf-telesales-int-acc3/shell/dbextract
 # Run the job bin/php73 DWHExtractCustomerAuthProcess.php --fullGenerate true
 # Extract the DWH file from below path  /opt/SP/websync/PRD_DATA/omnius/export/acc3/customer_auth
 # Validate the parameter in the file 

 

*Actual Result:* Cable customer authenticated using SPIN_CAB is not coming in the CSV file.

 

{*}Expected Result{*}: Cable customer authenticated using SPIN_CAB should be visible in the CSV file.

 

Test data:

KD_935049437>> SPIN_CAB

CSV file name: DWH..OMNIUS_EXTRACT_CUSTOMER_AUTHENTICATIONINFO.20240913142718.A901.csv

Please find the attached file and log

Current Behaviour :

*Valid for cable TV package*

*selbstInstallationKz = Y/N*
technician_needed_no - default = TECNOTV
technician_needed_yes - manual = 1V1 / VP0/ TECYESTV

*Valid for KIP package*

*selbstInstallationKz = Y*
technician_needed_no - default = TECNOKIP
technician_needed_yes - not shown in Dropdown

*selbstInstallationKz = N*
technician_needed_yes - default = TECYESKIP
technician_needed_no - not shown in Dropdown
h3. Expected Behaviour

*Valid for cable TV package*

*selbstInstallationKz* = Y/N AND *ABK* = J
technician_needed_yes  = 1V1 / {*}VP0{*}/ TECYESTV chargeable product should not be added in SC.

*selbstInstallationKz* = Y/N AND *ABK* = N - Remain as is (existing behaviour)
technician_needed_no - default = TECNOTV
technician_needed_yes - manual = 1V1 / {*}VP0{*}/ TECYESTV 

 

*Valid for KIP package*

*selbstInstallationKz* = Y/N AND *ABK* = J
technician_needed_yes - default and readonly = TECYESKIP chargeable product should not added in SC
technician_needed_no - not possbile as dropdown is freez

*selbstInstallationKz* = Y *AND* *ABK* = N - Remain as is (existing behaviour)

*Expected Result:*

column1: OSF | Wave 9.0 | CR716 Futurize | Regression | when booking 1st KIP (not Broadvision) and then TV, the technician option in the access details for KIP is displayed
column41:
Test data:
Environment: ACC2 (test1b) 

Channel: Retail + Telesales

OSE version: v9.19.2-BB1 2024-07-01 08:35 |07-09|03-03

Cable PCAT version: V2390_2024_07_00_076 

*{color:#172b4d}Please note:{color} when booking KIP (Broadvision) + TV, the technician option for KIP is not displayed - > OK*

*!image-2024-07-09-13-42-35-571.png!*

 

*Expected result corresponding to the requirement: [https://de.jira.agile.vodafone.com/browse/PORPDT-345]*

*When booking KIP + TV OR TV + KIP:*
 # *the Access Details for TV should not be displayed*
 # *the Access Details for KIP should be displayed but without the technician option*

 

{+}Actual result{+}: when booking 1st KIP (not Broadvision) and then TV, the technician option for KIP is displayed

+Expected result:+ when booking 1st KIP (not Broadvision) and then TV, the technician option for KIP should NOT be displayed

 

 

+Steps to reproduce:+
 * login to ACC2
 * search for a Cable address, e. g.: Hagelstangestr. 30, 81927 München
 * click on "Paket hinzufügen >> Kabel Internet & Phone"
 * select any KIP tariff ({*}NOT{*} {*}Broadvicion{*}), e. g.: a business tariff "[23C:24M] Red Business Internet 300 Cable netto 49,90 €"
 * click on "Paket hinzufügen >> Kabel TV"
 * select any TV tariff, e. g.: "[CGTH006] Vodafone GigaTV Home Cable - 6 Monate 9,99€, danach 14,99€"
 * click on the button "Weiter"
 * click on the button "Zum Checkout"
 * enter the customer data and click on the button "Weiter"

- > the technician option for KIP is displayed - > *NOT OK*

 

!image-2024-07-09-13-34-17-831.png!
column229: No Business Impact
column474: No fix necessary, because the use case from cable side changed so that the bug cannot occur anymore.
column779:
09/Jul/24 5:15 PM;natasa.dimovic1@vodafone.com;Analysis on PCAT side was done by [~tobias.pohlmann@vodafone.com] :

Hi, Ariadne,

{*}{color:#de350b}yes, I can confirm that in any case where we book KIP + TV (no matter if Broadvision or not, no matter which order we book it in), no technician section should be shown{color}{*}. 

The reason why this fails is as I tried to point out in my comment below. It really is pretty confusing, I apologize for that. I had a call with Natasa where I explained the problem, because it really is a bit hard to grasp.

So again in case of Broadvision what happens is:
 - [In the KIP package] KIP is booked, TV Connect is added because of Broadvision ---> OSF understands that no section for KIP should be shown because KIP + TV is booked and remembers that

 - [In the TV package] TV Digital is booked ---> OSF understands that no section for TV should be shown because KIP+TV is booked

==> no KIP or TV technician section is shown

In case of Not-Broadvision:
 - [In the KIP package] Only KIP is booked, but not TV yet ----> OSF supposes that a technician section should be shown for KIP (because only KIP is booked) and remembers that
 - [In the TV package] TV Digital + TV Connect is booked ----> OSF understands that no section for TV should be shown because KIP+TV is booked, but doesn't update the reasoning for KIP

==> technician section is shown for KIP, but not for TV;;;
column780:
10/Jul/24 8:34 PM;tobias.pohlmann@vodafone.com;Hi guys,

so, yesterday, we were asked by [~timo.russo@vodafone.com] to change the behaviour for KIP-only bookings, too; [[PSTBUG-2380] OSF_One Sehberetischaft option is available on NE3, NE4 VVO and MNV addresses in OSF while booking KIP only for new customers - DE Jira (vodafone.com).|https://de.jira.agile.vodafone.com/browse/PSTBUG-2380]

With this change (product setup version V2390_2024_07_00_086), this symptom here will not occur anymore, so I guess we could close this ticket. I apologize for the confusion.

But the underlying bug – OSF doesn't update the technician options it will display for KIP when it is currently in the TV package – still needs to be fixed as it is also the cause for https://jira.sp.vodafone.com/browse/OS-58440 .;;;

column783:
10/Jul/24 6:57 PM;sandeepkumar.pradhan@vodafone.com;Hi All,

{*}Why issue Occurred{*}: Since all the 3 field for CustomerDataHUB Solution1 Settings and CustomerDataHUB Settings  such as

CustomerDataHUB Solution1 Settings 
1)Central Search ES Interfaces Enabled

CustomerDataHUB Settings
1)Legacy search and MRT Enabled
2)Enable CDH Interface
are set to "Yes" which breaks the API flow in current OSE build  which is not the case in ACC1 or PROD
in both these environment at least one of the them or all are set as "NO" where both customer search and Installed base working fine (for PRODUCTION all filed set as NO)


{*}Action plan{*}: we need to work with Vodafone design team to understand on what criteria these all filed need to switch on (Set as yes) after that or parallelly we need look from OSE prospective how we can handle these API irrespective of setting (all 3 set to YES or all 3 set to NO(working condition) or partial set of YES and NO (working condition))
 

Also PROD and ACC2 are almost equal we should ensure that ACC2 setting always same that of PROD else conf change leads to issue like this , Do understand that tACC2 setting can be change too for testing but it has to be known to an extent;;;
column784:
11/Jul/24 12:02 PM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;[~sandeepkumar.pradhan@vodafone.com]  the settings on ACC and in PROD will never be exactly same, as we are always testing future topics in ACC which might not be live yet.
However, for these Fusion C switches we had topics in scope for different releases, so the functionality itself is live since a long time but with a technical go live.

1)[OS-8975] SOL0 - Search & display customer with product(s) mastered in solstice - Vodafone Global Jira -> implemented with Wave 7.0, tested with Wave 7.1  

2) [OS-11283] SOL1SE32 - Extending the OSF Search for Solstice Customers - Vodafone Global Jira -> initially implemented with Wave 7.2, because of needed enhancement tested again with Wave 9.0 

We are not having any new functionality, the switches are there since years. 
To retest your TechM fix for OS-56961 of course all switches had to be YES and in release Wave 9.0 they have been on YES in general most of the time, as OS-11283 was part of Wave 9.0 and tested by Fusion C team.

As ACC1 was used for Wave 8.2 of course ACC1 was different, as there only OS-8975 was live already (therefore only one switch was enabled) 

And as its technically live, Fusion C team can decide at any time to switch it ON in production. Its like any other technical go live, where functionaly is enabled in ACC but not yet in production.;;;

column1: ON-HOLD | OSF | Wave 9.0 | ACC2 | BEW version is getting updated in Unity backend, but cannot retrieve the GetPermissions because its not giving back the correct version
column41:
*Description:* For UM Scenario we observed issue as BEW version is not updating in Backend and BEW Erfassen is enable even after update the version.

 

*Test Data:*

281507501

*documentID:* 10832608

 

*Steps to reproduce:*

Login to Retail channel as FI/PA agent.
Search existing *UM* customer with ADV and DEV version less than 4.
Retrieve the customer and click on BEW Bearbeiten button.
Verify BEW banner notification.
Select BEW ERFASSEN.
Select checkbox for ADV/DEV.
Click on "Dokument erstellen"(Create document) button
Document will be generated.
After that search the customer again.
select BEW Bearbeiten button.
BEW Erfassen button should not available/disable.

 

*Actual Result:* BEW version is not updating in Backend and BEW Erfassen is enable, even after update the version.

*Expected Result:* BEW version should be update in Backend and BEW Erfassen button should be disable after updating the version.

 

*Reference Defect:*

[OS-56676]

column787:
11/Jul/24 7:56 PM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;[~rohan.kumbhar@vodafone.com]  based on the latest calls e have the following findings for Retail BEW and unitymedia in general

1) New customer, Retail, order + BEW -> Backend receives and stores BEW correctly

2) Existing customer, Retail, order + BEW -> Backend receives and stores BEW correctly

3) Existing customer, Retail, BEW only ->{color:#de350b} *Backend receives and stores BEW correctly? Please confirm this*
{color:#172b4d}What is wrong in all cases -> Frontend OSF is not able to retrieve the right BEW settings. So if BEW was updated in UNitymedia backend, Frontend is not reflecting this. It still looks like no BEW is set{color} ** 
{color:#172b4d}We will also compare the same for VKD, how Retrievecustomerinfo Mode 3 related to BEW permissions is looking like{color}{color};;;
column789:
12/Jul/24 7:08 PM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;[~rohan.kumbhar@vodafone.com]  the ticket itself is only for Unitymedia, so for VKD its not a problem and no ticket reported.

We still need to document here, if the Existing customer, Retail, BEW only for Unitymedia is reaching the backend as ticket says 

_*{color:#de350b}BEW version is not updating in Unity Backend{color}* and BEW Erfassen is enable even after update the version._

 

At the moment we assume, BEW version is getting updated in Unity backend, but we cannot retrieve the GetPermissions because its not giving back the correct version 
Unitymedia is handling permissions with Version 2, OGW expecting Version  4 and for retrieval of existing permissions we get Version 0.

Needs to be checked with responsible person from MinervaAdapter (VKD side);;;
column790: 17/Jul/24 2:34 PM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;No progress yet as we did not identify the responsible person who can help with Minerva Adapter VKD ;;;
column791:
18/Jul/24 9:28 PM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;I have enclosed the latest discussion.
As per latest analysis this problem is related to the way back from Unitymedia via Minerva Adapter VKD to OGW

{color:#de350b}*OK:*{color} OGW version 4 -> Minerva Adapter maps Version 4 from the VKD request into Version 2 for the request to UME/VFW -> UME/VFW is storing Version 2 correctly in Mood and showing right entries in RNS for the customer 

{color:#00875a}*Not OK*{color}: Now when we open the customer who has given BEW again in OSF, we expect that the stored BEW is taken and we are not asked to capture BEW again. Problem: For this get_permission Call we are receiving version 0 for the mentioned scenarios and we cannot map this version to our valid Version 4 (not OK)

{+}*Gap*{+}: We need a Mapping: UME/VFW is sending back Version 2 to Minerva Adapter-> Minerva Adapter maps Version 2 to Version 4 if getpermission request is coming from OGW

 

I have shared the feedback also with Jörg Trierweiler, Thomas Schneider, Andreas Baldermann and few more people to verify.
This is a general topic and not specifically related to BEW only Retail Epic
Waiting for feedback about possible next steps;;;

column41:

Steps to reproduce:

1) login to telesales/retail channel

2) perform customer search having existing customer Legacy / VC / VCP insurance

3) There customer should not see any new insurance options to select in configurator

 

 

Expected Result:

Existing customer having old Legacy or VC or VCP insurance should not be able to select any new insurance from configurator

 

Actual Result:

currently while performing ILS customer having any existing insurance can also see the different options to select from configurator.

column1: NEW CR OSF | ACC1 | Wave 8.2 | sliding prices are not interpreted as expected
column41:
{color:#ff0000}The priority is set to "Blocker" as the issue is a show stopper for the Go Live of : [https://de.jira.agile.vodafone.com/browse/PORPDT-79] 
Without a fix the feature can not be deployed into production.{color}

 

Test data:

Browser: Chrome
Environment: ACC1 
Channel: Telesales + Retail

Steps to reproduce the issue:
 - Enter address: Goethestr. 27 26409 Wittmund Wittmund
 - Select package: "Kabel Internet & Phone"
 - Select tariff: "[3BV:B09] GigaZuhause 250 Kabel, 1.-9. Monat 19,99 €"
 - Select goody on "Gutschriften und Aktionen" section: "[JL5] Gutschrift GigaZuhause Young: 1.-9. Monat: 0 €, 10.-24. Monat: -5 €, danach 0 €"
 - open basket

The prices are not calculated as expected.
As a consequence of the wrong basket also the contract summary is incorrect.

!image-2024-04-10-18-00-56-136.png|width=856,height=463!  

+Pre-Analyses of product configuration team:+
OSF uses the 'Price sliding' field from the Product Catalog to configure the way the price periods are shown in the frontend:

!screenshot-1.png|width=338,height=226!

The numbers in this field are however interpreted as absolute points in time. They should however be interpreted as relative time intervals.

+Concretely this means:+

Price sliding '9:6:' should be interpreted as 0.-9. month, 10.-15. month, 16. month onward.
Currently it is interpreted as 0.-9. month, 0.-6. month, whatever comes afterward.
This obviously does not make any sense, since the second period ends before the first one, so the consequence in the frontend is, that the second period is ignored.

+The obvious fix therefore is:+
The numbers in the "Price sliding" field should always be interpreted as *relative time* intervalls.

 

+Additional proof:+
When checking in the OSF Backoffice for the product properties, the price_sliding of JL5 looks like this:

!image-2024-04-09-15-34-39-869.png!

Looking at this in overview in the frontend, the second time intervall seems to be ignored:

!image-2024-04-10-18-00-56-136.png|width=423,height=229!

Manually changing it to 15 then leads to the following view in OSF:

!image-2024-04-09-15-42-29-039.png|width=737,height=206!

This is, however, still wrong. OSF seems to tread the numbers in the PCAT import as absolute times instead of relative intervals

=> Three sliding prices are in principle possible to show, but the configuration in the product setup is imported and interpreted wrongly
column106: 02/May/24 12:50 PM;stephanie.krammer@vodafone.com;OSF Incident Ticket - CRImprovement notwendig - OS-54646 OSF  ACC1  Wave 8.2  sliding prices are not interpreted as expected - Vodafone Global Jira.msg;https://jira.sp.vodafone.com/secure/attachment/1281954/OSF+Incident+Ticket+-+CRImprovement+notwendig+-+OS-54646+OSF++ACC1++Wave+8.2++sliding+prices+are+not+interpreted+as+expected+-+Vodafone+Global+Jira.msg

column820:
15/May/24 9:53 PM;ran.farjun1@vodafone.com;Hi,

yes, currently the fix is almost ready after discussions with design team and Ketaki.

in this fix the 24 retry will not be in use anymore, instead the retry will be determined by the ogw_error_handler table.

it will decide how many times to retry, and how much time to wait between the calls.

for this flow the retry will be active for empty response from oneDMS or OGWERR-9900 error code return

for example:
this is a record from the table:

{
    "ERROR_CODE":"OGWERR-9900",
    "ERROR_CATEGORY":"Technical",
    "IGNORE_ERROR_IND":"N",
    "RETRYABLE_IND":"TRUE",
    "MAX_RETRY_TIMES":"3",
    "RETRY_WAIT_TIME":"10",
    "MAX_WAIT_TIME":null,
    "STATUS_TO_SET":null,
    "CHANNEL":"TELESALES",
    "SERVICE_CALL":"ASYNC",
    "SERVICE_NAME":"OneDMS"
}
so the flow will retry 3 times and the wait time will be 10 seconds between every try.;;;

column41:
Test data:
Environment: ACC1 (test2b) 

Channel: Retail + Telesales

{+}Actual result{+}: For VKD KUD customers on a Unity address the SPIN is not recognized

 

+Expected result:+ For VKD KUD customers on a Unity address the SPIN should be recognized

column805:
18/Apr/24 12:36 PM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;There was a meeting between Kshitij and Andreas with following outcome:
 * Values like "AccountCategory" in Omnius are derived from OGW: Here:- _AccountCategory_ in getCustomerResult for index search and _Region_ in retrieveCustomerInfo mode1 for LegacySearch.
 * As the ADDRESS REGION is in UM Area - it is treated as UM customer, even though he belongs to the VKD Stack

h4. _Possible SD option to be validated/proven:_ 
 * Derive customer stack from GlobalID prefix ("legacy stack")  instead of address region
 * IF improvements required as this is only known by OGW (Omnius can only see LK_ from linked customers) - e.g. introducing new attribute to indicate customers product stack:
 * CustomerSearch()
 * getCustomerDetails()
 * [@Mitra, Gaurab, External Vendor|mailto:gaurab.mitra@amdocs.com]: We should investigate if further interfaces have to be considered (To be discussed on next CR meeting)

[@Kshitij.Srivastava@comviva.com|mailto:kshitij.srivastava@comviva.com]: To check UseCases in Omnius to be considered for an improvement

Further benefit: Omnius Performance increase If product stack information is directly provided by OGW 

 

So team is working on possible solution but will take some time ;;;

column786:
24/Jan/24 3:56 PM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;[~vikash.saurav@vodafone.com]  I was not creating any order, I am just scanning portal UI tool from time to time to find unidentified issues. And within this quality check I have found tickets with this error message. 

 

After some analysis I have identified, that it seems to be this scenario:

-> Search existing unitymedia customer and perform Move to VKD adress 

 

this is example Order ID from ACC1 - it failed with 2 sky tickets

One ticket because of invalid VPKN (issue is solved, please ignore that) and second sky ticket was for setpermission.


Unfortunately Sky ticket were cleared in between so I am not able to find my two tickets anymore..... But hopefully you can reproduce on your environment for a Move from Unity to VKD.

Seems like in this case the existing customer ID from unity is taken over, instead of recognizing that customer will get a new customer ID from VKD for Move scenario

 

Order ID 782545, Customer ID 1009755201 (initial customer before Move) 

!image-2024-01-24-11-21-17-927.png!

 

Same seems to happen when moving from Unity Cable to DSL product. 

So please check flow Unity Cable to VKD Cable Move, and Unity Cable to DSL Move

 ;;;

column1: OSF | CR716 Wave8.2 | ACC1 | Unitymedia | Error message is displayed in Access details if order placed in NE3 Address with self install =no
column41:
We tried placing an order with NE3 Address where Self install is no (ACC1)

in Access details we are getting the below error

({*}Your technical connection selection does not match){*}

!image-2023-12-15-18-50-55-105.png|width=406,height=222!

 

 

Steps to Recreate:

1)Take an address with NE3 and Self install=no(Example:51063,Köln ,Von-Galen-Str. 63) in unitymedia region

2)Select any of  the KIP Product(TV Will get added automatically)

3)checkout and move forward

4)check whether any error message is shown in Access Details

 

Actual: Error message is shown at access details page

Expected: No error message should be shown in Access details page 

Note:If we change the access details option to technician required for TV product then we are able to move forward without any issue
column229: Agent might get confused with the error message in connection selection and needs to use some workaround to be able to proceed (only NE3 Address where Self install is no is affected)
column474: Fixed - new requirements

[https://de.jira.agile.vodafone.com/browse/SYSSHARQS-1699]

Small description of Teststeps:
Testcustomer: *934829320* (has an old TV product CGT1WG1)
Open OSF ACC2 Telesales
Load Testcustomer
Add a mobile tariff like *[KGM1LH30] GigaMobil L mit PremiumSmartphoneSpecial (Sub 30)*
With hardware "{*}[S00302349] Oppo Find X3 Pro Navy Blue - M{*}"
Go to the existing products of the customer
and click on Paket ändern
TV is opened

column474: Logic for Gigakombi was changed & there is no GigaKombi available for TV. The markers VB4 + VB5 are not booked anymore. Also for KIP there wsa a change. VA1 was replaced with GKF and GKF is not booked for existing customers. Therefore the defect is not reproducible anymore
column774: As a workaround the agent can trigger execution of the posting rules by selecting and deselecting any product.
column779:
21/Nov/23 6:51 PM;johannes-alexander.dengler@vodafone.com;Analysis results:

To prevent more issues related to [[OTF-902] KIPOPENEDMARKER not being sent in submit order xml || ADD and Drop Cable backend error - Vodafone Global Jira|https://jira.sp.vodafone.com/browse/OTF-902] we improved the detection of empty packages in OSF to prevent the agent from entering the checkout with such.

In this case however the package is not empty as it contains VB4. As such our rule should not trigger if the posting rules were executed correctly after clicking the button to create the GigaKombi bundle.

This issue must be fixed by OSF - the posting must be executed after the bundle is created and a product (like VB4) is added to the package.;;;

column801:
13/Dec/23 4:42 PM;simon.auch@vodafone.com;As explained in the call (and in previous comments on this ticket):
 * the checkout is blocked by a rule that comes from the pcat because the product OMNIUSTVCHANGEDMARKER is not selected.
 * the product is added by the posting rules of the cable rules artifact if there is _any_ change to the TV package
 * after the bundle is created the TV package _is changed as it now contains VB4_
 * as checked in the logs: the posting rules are not called by OSF after the bundle is created

*OSF has to call the posting rules after any change to a cable package, otherwise inconsistencies regarding products/orders/etc are to be expected.* ;;;
column802:
14/Dec/23 1:55 PM;bharath.krishnamurthy@vodafone.com;[~johannes-alexander.dengler@vodafone.com] [~simon.auch@vodafone.com] 

 
Hari Shankar Malviya 
added a comment -
 
Hi Alexander/Simon,
 
 For extended shopping cart min max equal warning rules, there is not relation with cable post rule results or execution.
The rule which is problematic, is a max(0) rule and service to category rule. So if this rule’s service source expression evaluates to true than it will check if cart have max 0 number of products only from the target category. So if product OMNIUSTVCHANGEDMARKER is not part of the package then problematic rule service source expression will evaluate to true and further it will show warning if from target category we have more then 0 products in cart.;;;

14/Dec/23 4:54 PM;simon.auch@vodafone.com;[~ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com], I am not sure if there was any more specific documentation (I will keep searching for a bit), but the following HLD already has a section:
|*Cable artifact rules*
 
The Cable Catalog and PLM colleagues have requested their own rules engine to be applied in the configurator. This is realised with a plugin development where Cable colleagues can upload their Rules Artifact as part of the PLM process. This Rules Artifact consists of the same Sales Rules (in PHP language/cable-speak) that is used currently in ECC front-ends. OMNIUS will share the full-shoppingcart (all packages) to the Rules Artifact, the rules artifact will process ruling, and return the shoppingcart object with modified cable orderlines in Kabel TV, KIP and KUD packages to be displayed in OMNIUS. The Rules Artifact will be called both before a product is selected (on show of configurator, pre-condition) {*}as well as after selecting a product (on adding to the shoppingcart, post-condition){*}. OMNIUS will not be able to have special GUI handling like for internal OMNIUS sales rules when using the Artifact.|

Highlighting added by me.

Full document: [https://vodafone.sharepoint.com/sites/C3-B2B-OneSalesFoundation/IMPLEMENTATION%20Drop1/Deliverables/01%20V-HLD%20Vertical%20HLDs/HLD%202.0/V-HLD_01_Workpackage%201_Scenario%201c-v2%2018.docx]

 

From a slightly newer HLD:
|Apart from the Omnius compatibility rules for cable, specific precondition and postcondition rules from cable are also evaluated within the Cable Rules Artifact. *With each change in the configurator (for cable products) the Omnius rules and Cable rules artifact are evaluated in a loop, until a stable state is reached.* |

Full document: [https://vodafone.sharepoint.com/sites/C3-B2B-OneSalesFoundation/IMPLEMENTATION%20Drop1/Deliverables/02%20FA/FA-01%20Product%20Catalogue/FA-01_30%20HLD%20Wave%203_Product%20Catalogue-v2.11.docx]

Also present in a newer version: https://vodafone.sharepoint.com/sites/C3-B2B-OneSalesFoundation/IMPLEMENTATION%20Drop1/Deliverables/02%20FA/FA-01%20Product%20Catalogue/FA-01_40%20HLD%20Wave%204%20Product%20Catalogue-v2.3.docx

column41:

Existing Unitymedia cable customer with following inventory: legacy KIP Product (not Broadvision) and legacy TV Product (Code UMDKLM) orders GigaZuhause 1000 (Broadvision product) - Telesales

column779:
09/Nov/23 7:56 PM;johannes-alexander.dengler@vodafone.com;From what I can see in VkdGateway the price of the product is correctly returned as:

"nonStandardRate": 17.64, 

which with VAT makes ~20.99€.

The product itself however does not seem to indicate that it has a price nor a non standard rate, both of which should however not be necessary for unity inventory products.

It is noteworthy that the product itself has no price configured in the product setup, maybe the display in the contract summary of OSF does not work if it is an inventory product without a price (and without a non standard rate actually configured in the product setup)?

To me this sounds a) like an OSF issue and b) not like a BV issue.;;;

select the Experten-Service Einrichtung for any Broadband Order:

 * click on the button "Zum Checkout"
 * fill in the customer data
 * click on the button "Weiter"

– > Check which option is selected in Access details

OGW:2695200

21/Sep/23 4:46 PM;simon.auch@vodafone.com;According to the answer from [~vikash.saurav@vodafone.com]  https://jira.sp.vodafone.com/browse/OS-42115?focusedId=2910953&page=com.atlassian.jira.plugin.system.issuetabpanels:comment-tabpanel#comment-2910953 the display of the tv access details depends on the availability of the products TECNOTV and TECYESTV reported by the cable logic.

*Open questions from my perspective:*
 * which products exactly control the display of the tv access details in OSF?
 ** Is it only TECYESTV and TECNOTV or also products like VP0, 1V1?
 ** Is this controlled by special tags on products or categories, or are the products hardcoded in OSF?
Maybe [~vikash.saurav@vodafone.com] can answer this question?
 * If the display of the checkout part is only controlled by TECYESTV and TECNOTV, this will not work (and from cable side never should have) for Unity, since these two products are not aligned and should never be available for Unity.
Which TV technician option should be bookable in Unity TV scenarios? As far as I am aware there is no TV technician product that is available in the Unity footprint.
 *  in which scenarios should which technician option be bookable in OSF?

 * 
 ** we have a list of ~80 test cases. Some of these are apparently not correct.
 ** Who can go through these test cases with us and determine which of them need to be changed?
 ** Without at least a contact person that can answer this question it will not make sense to start implementation of this ticket.
